# Knowledge Self Update Rule

.ai-agent is the single source of project AI knowledge. Keep it current.

## Must Update Knowledge When

- adding/removing/moving a module, route, page, component, hook, store module, service, or util;
- changing an API/service contract, route/query contract, event contract, store data flow, or shared hook signature;
- introducing a reusable UI/UX interaction pattern;
- fixing a bug that creates a stable future constraint;
- discovering stale project map entries while editing code.

## Where To Update

Use .ai-agent/project-skills/aafe-self-update/SKILL.md as the routing table.
Common targets:

- architecture/module map -> .ai-agent/project-skills/bklog-architecture/SKILL.md
- components -> .ai-agent/project-skills/bklog-components/SKILL.md
- APIs/services -> .ai-agent/project-skills/bklog-api-services/SKILL.md
- hooks -> .ai-agent/project-skills/bklog-hooks/SKILL.md
- coding conventions -> .ai-agent/project-skills/bklog-coding-patterns/SKILL.md
- stable UI/performance constraints -> .ai-agent/rules/*.mdc
- reusable decisions/lessons -> .ai-agent/memory/*.md

## Constraints

- Do not recreate or reference the legacy shared AI directory.
- Do not duplicate project knowledge in .cursor or .codebuddy; those files only point to .ai-agent.
- Keep knowledge updates concise: navigation hints, contracts, boundaries, and change impact only.
- If no knowledge update is needed, state why in the final response.
